The paper focuses on analyzing the accuracy of the fault-prediction model proposed by SonarQube, which is a tool used for analyzing Technical Debt in software development. This falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves the use of Machine Learning techniques to compare the classification power of different models, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The study involves analyzing data from open-source projects, which falls under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also involves evaluating the effectiveness of coding rules, which falls under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves empirical research, which falls under Machine Learning (cs.LG).
